.TH "regulator_set_current_limit" 9 "regulator_set_current_limit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
regulator_set_current_limit \- set regulator output current limit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" regulator_set_current_limit
.BI "(struct regulator *regulator "  ","
.BI "int min_uA "  ","
.BI "int max_uA "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "regulator" 12
regulator source
.IP "min_uA" 12
Minimum supported current in uA
.IP "max_uA" 12
Maximum supported current in uA
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets current sink to the desired output current. This can be set during
any regulator state. IOW, regulator can be disabled or enabled.

If the regulator is enabled then the current will change to the new value
immediately otherwise if the regulator is disabled the regulator will
output at the new current when enabled.
.SH "NOTE"
Regulator system constraints must be set for this regulator before
calling this function otherwise this call will fail.
